.6.4" \w* \w  and my body  |strong="1320" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.6.5" \w* \w  trembles in horror .  |strong="6427" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.6.6" \w* \v 7 \w  Why  |strong="4069" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.7.1" \w* \w  do the wicked  |strong="7563" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.7.2" \w* \w  live on ,  |strong="2421" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.7.3" \w* \w  growing old  |strong="6275" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.7.4" \w* \w  and  |strong="1571" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.7.5" \w* \w  increasing  |strong="1396" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.7.6" \w* \w  in power ?  |strong="2428" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.7.7" \w* \v 8 \w  Their descendants  |strong="2233" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.8.1" \w* \w  are established  |strong="3559" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.8.2" \w* \w  around them  |strong="5973" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.8.4" \w* \w  . . . ,  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.8.3" \w* \w  and their offspring  |strong="6631" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.8.5" \w* \w  before their eyes .  |strong="5869" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.8.6" \w* \v 9 \w  Their homes  |strong="1004" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.9.1" \w* \w  are safe  |strong="7965" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.9.2" \w* \w  from fear ;  |strong="6343" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.9.3" \w* \w  no  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.9.4" \w* \w  rod of punishment  |strong="7626" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.9.5" \w* \w  from God  |strong="433" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.9.6" \w* \w  [is] upon them .  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.9.7" \w* \v 10 \w  Their bulls  |strong="7794" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.10.1" \w* \w  breed  |strong="5674" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.10.2" \w* \w  without  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.10.3" \w* \w  fail ;  |strong="1602" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.10.4" \w* \w  their cows  |strong="6510" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.10.6" \w* \w  bear calves  |strong="6403" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.10.5" \w* \w  and do not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.10.7" \w* \w  miscarry .  |strong="7921" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.10.8" \w* \v 11 \w  They send forth  |strong="7971" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.11.1" \w* \w  their little ones  |strong="5759" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.11.3" \w* \w  like a flock ;  |strong="6629" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.11.2" \w* \w  their children  |strong="3206" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.11.4" \w* \w  skip about ,  |strong="7540" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.11.5" \w* \v 12 \w  singing  |strong="5375" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.12.1" \w* \w  to the tambourine  |strong="8596" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.12.2" \w* \w  and lyre  |strong="3658" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.12.3" \w* \w  and making merry  |strong="8055" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.12.4" \w* \w  at the sound  |strong="6963" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.12.5" \w* \w  of the flute .  |strong="5748" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.12.6" \w* \v 13 \w  They spend  |strong="1086" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.13.1" \w* \w  their days  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.13.3" \w* \w  in prosperity  |strong="2896" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.13.2" \w* \w  and go down  |strong="5181" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.13.6" \w* \w  to Sheol  |strong="7585" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.13.5" \w* \w  in peace .  |strong="7281" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.13.4" \w* \v 14 \w  Yet they say  |strong="559" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.14.1" \w* \w  to God :  |strong="410" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.14.2" \w* \w  ‘ Leave us alone  |strong="5493" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.14.3" \w* \w  . . . !  |strong="4480" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.14.4" \w* \w  For we have no  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.14.7" \w* \w  desire  |strong="2654" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.14.8" \w* \w  to know  |strong="1847" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.14.5" \w* \w  Your ways .  |strong="1870" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.14.6" \w* \v 15 \w  Who  |strong="4100" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.15.1" \w* \w  is the Almighty ,  |strong="7706" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.15.2" \w* \w  that  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.15.3" \w* \w  we should serve Him ,  |strong="5647" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.15.4" \w* \w  and what  |strong="4100" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.15.5" \w* \w  would we gain  |strong="3276" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.15.6" \w* \w  if  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.15.7" \w* \w  we pray  |strong="6293" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.15.8" \w* \w  to Him ? ’  |srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.15.9" \w* \v 16 \w  Still ,  |strong="2005" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.16.1" \w* \w  their prosperity [is]  |strong="2898" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.16.4" \w* \w  not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.16.2" \w* \w  in their own hands ,  |strong="3027" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.16.3" \w* \w  so I stay far  |strong="7368" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.16.7" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="4480" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.16.8" \w* \w  from the counsel  |strong="6098" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.16.5" \w* \w  of the wicked .  |strong="7563" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.16.6" \w* \v 17 \w  How often  |strong="4100" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.17.1" \w* \w  is the lamp  |strong="5216" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.17.2" \w* \w  of the wicked  |strong="7563" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.17.3" \w* \w  put out ?  |strong="1846" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.17.4" \w* \w  Does disaster  |strong="343" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.17.7" \w* \w  come  |strong="935" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.17.5" \w* \w  upon them ?  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.17.6" \w* \w  Does [God,] in His anger ,  |strong="639" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.17.10" \w* \w  apportion  |strong="2505" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.17.9" \w* \w  destruction ?  |strong="2256" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.17.8" \w* \v 18 \w  Are  |strong="1961" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.18.1" \w* \w  they like straw  |strong="8401" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.18.2" \w* \w  before  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.18.3" \w* \w  the wind ,  |strong="7307" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.18.4" \w* \w  like chaff  |strong="4671" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.18.5" \w* \w  swept away  |strong="1589" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.18.6" \w* \w  by a storm ?  |strong="5492" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.18.7" \w* \v 19 \w  [It is said that] God  |strong="433" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.19.1" \w* \w  lays up  |strong="6845" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.19.2" \w* \w  one’s punishment  |strong="205" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.19.4" \w* \w  for his children .  |strong="1121" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.19.3" \w* \w  Let God repay the man  |strong="7999" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.19.5" \w* \w  himself ,  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.19.6" \w* \w  so he will know it .  |strong="3045" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.19.7" \w* \v 20 \w  Let his eyes  |strong="5869" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.20.2" \w* \w  see  |strong="7200" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.20.1" \w* \w  his own destruction ;  |strong="3589" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.20.3" \w* \w  let him drink [for himself]  |strong="8354" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.20.6" \w* \w  the wrath  |strong="2534" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.20.4" \w* \w  of the Almighty .  |strong="7706" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.20.5" \w* \v 21 \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.21.1" \w* \w  what  |strong="4100" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.21.2" \w* \w  does he care  |strong="2656" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.21.3" \w* \w  about his household  |strong="1004" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.21.4" \w* \w  after him ,  |strong="310" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.21.5" \w* \w  when the number  |strong="4557" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.21.6" \w* \w  of his months  |strong="2320" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.21.7" \w* \w  has run out ?  |strong="2686" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.21.8" \w* \v 22 \w  Can anyone teach  |strong="3925" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.22.2" \w* \w  knowledge  |strong="1847" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.22.3" \w* \w  to God ,  |strong="410" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.22.1" \w* \w  since He  |strong="1931" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.22.4" \w* \w  judges  |strong="8199" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.22.6" \w* \w  those on high ?  |strong="7311" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.22.5" \w* \v 23 \w  One man  |strong="2088" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.23.1" \w* \w  dies  |strong="4191" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.23.2" \w* \w  full of vigor  |strong="6106" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.23.3" \w* \w  . . . ,  |strong="8537" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.23.4" \w* \w  completely  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.23.5" \w* \w  secure  |strong="7946" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.23.6" \w* \w  and at ease .  |strong="7961" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.23.7" \w* \v 24 \w  His body  |strong="5845" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.24.1" \w* \w  is well nourished  |strong="4390" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.24.2" \w* \w  . . . ,  |strong="2461" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.24.3" \w* \w  and his bones  |strong="6106" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.24.5" \w* \w  [are] rich  |strong="8248" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.24.6" \w* \w  with marrow .  |strong="4221" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.24.4" \w* \v 25 \w  Yet another man  |strong="2088" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.25.1" \w* \w  dies  |strong="4191" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.25.2" \w* \w  in the bitterness  |strong="4751" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.25.4" \w* \w  of his soul ,  |strong="5315" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.25.3" \w* \w  having never  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.25.5" \w* \w  tasted  |strong="398" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.25.6" \w* \w  prosperity .  |strong="2896" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.25.7" \w* \v 26 \w  But together  |strong="3162" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.26.1" \w* \w  they lie down  |strong="7901" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.26.4" \w* \w  in  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.26.2" \w* \w  the dust ,  |strong="6083" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.26.3" \w* \w  and worms  |strong="7415" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.26.5" \w* \w  cover them  |strong="3680" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.26.6" \w* \w  [both] .  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.26.7" \w* \v 27 \w  Behold ,  |strong="2005" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.27.1" \w* \w  I know  |strong="3045" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.27.2" \w* \w  your thoughts full well ,  |strong="4284" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.27.3" \w* \w  the schemes by which  |strong="4209" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.27.4" \w* \w  you would wrong  |strong="2554" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.27.6" \w* \w  me .  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.27.5" \w* \v 28 \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.28.1" \w* \w  you say ,  |strong="559" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.28.2" \w* \w  ‘ Where  |strong="346" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.28.3" \w* \w  now is the nobleman’s  |strong="5081" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.28.5" \w* \w  house ,  |strong="1004" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.28.4" \w* \w  and where  |strong="346" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.28.6" \w* \w  are the tents  |strong="168" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.28.7" \w* \w  in which the wicked  |strong="7563" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.28.9" \w* \w  dwell ? ’  |strong="4908" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.28.8" \w* \v 29 \w  Have you never  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.29.1" \w* \w  asked  |strong="7592" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.29.2" \w* \w  those who travel  |strong="5674" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.29.3" \w* \w  the roads ?  |strong="1870" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.29.4" \w* \w  Do you not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.29.6" \w* \w  accept  |strong="5234" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.29.7" \w* \w  their reports ?  |strong="226" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.29.5" \w* \v 30 \w  Indeed ,  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.30.1" \w* \w  the evil  |strong="7451" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.30.5" \w* \w  man is spared  |strong="2820" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.30.4" \w* \w  from the day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.30.2" \w* \w  of calamity ,  |strong="343" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.30.3" \w* \w  delivered  |strong="2986" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.30.8" \w* \w  from the day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.30.6" \w* \w  of wrath .  |strong="5678" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.30.7" \w* \v 31 \w  Who  |strong="4310" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.31.1" \w* \w  denounces  |strong="5046" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.31.2" \w* \w  his behavior  |strong="1870" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.31.5" \w* \w  to  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.31.3" \w* \w  his face ?  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.31.4" \w* \w  Who  |strong="4310" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.31.8" \w* \w  repays  |strong="7999" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.31.9" \w* \w  him  |srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.31.10" \w* \w  for what he  |strong="1931" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.31.6" \w* \w  has done ?  |strong="6213" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.31.7" \w* \v 32 \w  He  |strong="1931" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.32.1" \w* \w  is carried  |strong="2986" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.32.3" \w* \w  to the grave ,  |strong="6913" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.32.2" \w* \w  and watch is kept  |strong="8245" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.32.6" \w* \w  over  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.32.4" \w* \w  his tomb .  |strong="1430" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.32.5" \w* \v 33 \w  The clods  |strong="7263" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.3" \w* \w  of the valley  |strong="5158" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.4" \w* \w  are sweet  |strong="4985" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.1" \w* \w  to him ;  |srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.2" \w* \w  everyone  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.6" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="120" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.7" \w* \w  follows  |strong="4900" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.8" \w* \w  behind him ,  |strong="310" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.5" \w* \w  and those before him  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.9" \w* \w  are without  |strong="369" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.10" \w* \w  number .  |strong="4557" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.33.11" \w* \v 34 \w  So how  |strong="349" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.34.1" \w* \w  can you comfort me  |strong="5162" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.34.2" \w* \w  with empty words ?  |strong="1892" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.34.3" \w* \w  For your answers  |strong="8666" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.34.4" \w* \w  remain  |strong="7604" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.34.5" \w* \w  [full of] falsehood . ”  |strong="4604" srcloc="WLC:JOB.21.34.6" \w* 
