\p
\v 1 \w  [“] Why  |strong="4069" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.1.1" \w* \w  does the Almighty  |strong="7706" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.1.2" \w* \w  not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.1.3" \w* \w  reserve  |strong="6845" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.1.4" \w* \w  times for judgment ?  |strong="6256" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.1.5" \w* \w  Why may those who know Him  |strong="3045" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.1.6" \w* \w  never  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.1.7" \w* \w  see  |strong="2372" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.1.8" \w* \w  His days ?  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.1.9" \w* \v 2 \w  Men move  |strong="5381" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.2.2" \w* \w  boundary stones ;  |strong="1367" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.2.1" \w* \w  they pasture  |strong="7462" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.2.5" \w* \w  stolen  |strong="1497" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.2.4" \w* \w  flocks .  |strong="5739" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.2.3" \w* \v 3 \w  They drive away  |strong="5090" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.3.3" \w* \w  the donkey  |strong="2543" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.3.1" \w* \w  of the fatherless  |strong="3490" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.3.2" \w* \w  and take the widow’s  |strong="490" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.3.6" \w* \w  ox  |strong="7794" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.3.5" \w* \w  in pledge .  |strong="2254" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.3.4" \w* \v 4 \w  They push  |strong="5186" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.4.1" \w* \w  the needy  |strong="34" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.4.2" \w* \w  off the road  |strong="1870" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.4.3" \w* \w  and force all  |strong="3162" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.4.4" \w* \w  the poor  |strong="6035" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.4.6" \w* \w  of the land  |strong="776" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.4.7" \w* \w  into hiding .  |strong="2244" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.4.5" \w* \v 5 \w  Indeed ,  |strong="2005" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.1" \w* \w  [like] wild donkeys  |strong="6501" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.2" \w* \w  in the desert ,  |strong="4057" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.3" \w* \w  the poor go  |strong="3318" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.4" \w* \w  to work  |strong="6467" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.5" \w* \w  foraging  |strong="7836" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.6" \w* \w  for food ;  |strong="2964" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.7" \w* \w  the wasteland  |strong="6160" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.8" \w* \w   |srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.9" \w* \w  is food  |strong="3899" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.10" \w* \w  for their children .  |strong="5288" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.5.11" \w* \v 6 \w  They gather  |strong="7114" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.6.3" \w* \w  fodder  |strong="1098" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.6.2" \w* \w  in the fields  |strong="7704" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.6.1" \w* \w  and glean  |strong="3953" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.6.6" \w* \w  the vineyards  |strong="3754" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.6.4" \w* \w  of the wicked .  |strong="7563" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.6.5" \w* \v 7 \w  Without  |strong="1097" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.7.3" \w* \w  clothing ,  |strong="3830" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.7.4" \w* \w  they spend the night  |strong="3885" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.7.2" \w* \w  naked ;  |strong="6174" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.7.1" \w* \w  they have no  |strong="369" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.7.5" \w* \w  covering  |strong="3682" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.7.6" \w* \w  against the cold .  |strong="7135" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.7.7" \w* \v 8 \w  Drenched  |strong="7372" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.8.3" \w* \w  by mountain  |strong="2022" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.8.2" \w* \w  rains ,  |strong="2230" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.8.1" \w* \w  they huddle  |strong="2263" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.8.6" \w* \w  against the rocks  |strong="6697" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.8.7" \w* \w  for want  |strong="1097" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.8.4" \w* \w  of shelter .  |strong="4268" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.8.5" \w* \v 9 \w  The fatherless infant  |strong="3490" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.9.3" \w* \w  is snatched  |strong="1497" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.9.1" \w* \w  from the breast ;  |strong="7699" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.9.2" \w* \w  the nursing child  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.9.4" \w* \w  of the poor  |strong="6041" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.9.5" \w* \w  is seized for a debt .  |strong="2254" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.9.6" \w* \v 10 \w  Without  |strong="1097" srcloc="WLC:JOB.24.10.3" \w* \w  clothing ,  |strong="3830" srcl